00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:41,708
<i>REBECCA HAS TWO OFFERS</i>
<i>ON THE TABLE‐‐</i>

00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:43,710
<i>KEVIN HARRINGTON HAS OFFERED</i>
<i>$100,000</i>

00:10:43,710 --> 00:10:47,747
<i>FOR 40% OF HER BUSINESS,</i>
<i>WHILE BARBARA HAS OFFERED</i>

00:10:47,747 --> 00:10:50,183
<i>THE SAME AMOUNT,</i>
<i>BUT FOR ONLY 15%.</i>

00:10:50,183 --> 00:10:52,952
<i>HOWEVER, BARBARA'S OFFER</i>
<i>COMES WITH A CONDITION</i>

00:10:52,952 --> 00:10:55,922
<i>THAT HER PARTNER IN NEW YORK</i>
<i>WILL ALSO WANT TO INVEST.</i>

00:10:55,922 --> 00:10:57,991
REBECCA,
I'M READY TO DO THIS DEAL.

00:10:57,991 --> 00:11:00,994
I'M READY TO PRODUCE THE TV
COMMERCIAL, BUY THE MEDIA,

00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:03,329
AND GET THIS INTO
EVERY PET STORE IN AMERICA.

00:11:03,329 --> 00:11:06,332
I THINK YOU'RE HEARING
FROM BARBARA, SHE HAS TO GO

00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:09,102
TO SOMEBODY WHO'S GONNA MAYBE
SAY YES AND MAYBE SAY NO.

00:11:09,102 --> 00:11:13,239
YOU'RE HERE TO DO A DEAL TODAY.
I'M READY TO DO A DEAL.

00:11:13,239 --> 00:11:16,176
I THINK YOU'RE A GREAT PARTNER
FOR THIS,

00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:18,845
BUT AT 40% FOR $100,000,
I CAN'T DO IT.

00:11:18,845 --> 00:11:21,447
IT'S NOT IN THE BEST INTEREST
FOR CitiKitty.

00:11:21,447 --> 00:11:23,583
I MADE $100,000 LAST YEAR ALONE,

00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:26,519
AND THAT PRODUCT WASN'T
EVEN IN RETAIL YET.

00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:30,490
GIVE ME A COUNTEROFFER.

00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:34,827
20% AT $100,000.

00:11:34,827 --> 00:11:39,032
YOU ARE ONE SHREWD CAT.

00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:43,169
$100,000, 25%.
THAT'S IT.

00:11:43,169 --> 00:11:44,804
UM...

00:11:44,804 --> 00:11:47,807
LET ME JUST REMIND YOU THAT
EVERY TIME I JUMPED INTO BED

00:11:47,807 --> 00:11:50,710
WITH A GUY IN A BUSINESS DEAL,

00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:53,012
IT WAS SWEET IN THE BEGINNING.

00:11:53,012 --> 00:11:55,215
IT NEVER WOUND UP
IN A GOOD PLACE.

00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:58,484
WHY DO YOU ALWAYS
BRING IT BACK TO SEX?
YOU USE SEX.
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'D SAY THAT.

00:11:58,484 --> 00:12:01,888
(Barbara) THIS ISN'T ABOUT SEX.
UM...

00:12:01,888 --> 00:12:05,225
YOU WANT TO THINK ABOUT IT
AND COME BACK?
NO, NO, NO.

00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:08,228
(Harrington) DON'T MAKE
THE WRONG MOVE.
NO, NO. NO, IF I WALK OUT HERE,
THERE'S DAGGERS IN MY BACK.

00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:11,231
(Daymond) SHE MUST KNOW US.
IT'S TIME TO MAKE A DECISION.

00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:14,234
IT'S JUST NOT... OH.

00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:17,337
KEVIN, I KNOW THAT YOU ARE
THE GURU FOR AS SEEN ON TV,

00:12:17,337 --> 00:12:19,572
BUT I LIKE BARBARA.
I LIKE THE FEMALE TOUCH.

00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:22,942
(groans)
(speaks indistinctly) I'M
A FEMALE. LOOK AT ME. BIG SELL.

00:12:22,942 --> 00:12:25,678
SHE'S TRYING TO PLAY IT UP.
SHE'S SO SEXIST.

00:12:25,678 --> 00:12:28,114
BUT THERE'S ALWAYS BEEN
SOMETHING ABOUT BARBARA

00:12:28,114 --> 00:12:31,484
THAT YOU CAN'T TURN AWAY FROM,
AND IT'S‐‐IT'S A HEART. I MEAN‐‐
YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S CALLED?
IT'S CALLED TRUST.

00:12:31,484 --> 00:12:33,653
AND YOU'RE RIGHT.
OH, COME ON!

00:12:33,653 --> 00:12:35,722
(Daymond and O'Leary groan)

00:12:35,722 --> 00:12:38,725
LOOK, YOU KNOW, WE CAN'T SPEND
THE REST OF OUR LIVES HERE.

00:12:38,725 --> 00:12:42,562
YOUR CAT'S GONNA BE DEAD
BY THE TIME YOU GET HOME.

00:12:42,562 --> 00:12:45,398
I WOULD DO‐‐
I WOULD DO 20% AT $100,000.

00:12:45,398 --> 00:12:48,167
I LOVE YOU, BARBARA,
BUT I WOULD DO THAT.
OH.

00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:52,105
ALWAYS ABOUT MONEY.
DON'T DO IT, BECAUSE I'M GONNA
DROP THE CONTINGENCY,

00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:54,741
JUST TO KNOCK HIM
OUT OF THE BOX.
(gasps) WHY?

00:12:54,741 --> 00:12:57,910
YOU ARE A WITCH, BARBARA.
I'M NOT A WITCH.

00:12:57,910 --> 00:13:00,280
CAN'T WE WORK TOGETHER?
I KNOW YOU GUYS HAVE

00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:03,283
WORKED TOGETHER BEFORE.
CAN WE WORK TOGETHER? I‐I‐I...
I THINK WE STAND ALONE
ON THIS DEAL.

00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:05,718
OHH!
(Daymond) OHH!

00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:07,720
IF YOU DON'T MAKE A DECISION,

00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:10,723
I'M TAKING A CONTRACT OUT
ON YOUR CAT. YOU GET HOME,

00:13:10,723 --> 00:13:13,126
HE'LL BE MISSING.
YOU'VE GOT THE SOLID TV GUY

00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:15,128
AND THE WITCH SNAKE.

00:13:15,128 --> 00:13:18,131
I DON'T THINK THERE'S A DECISION
TO BE MADE RIGHT HERE.

00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:21,601
SO NOW I'M SAYING I'LL GIVE YOU
THE $100,000 FOR THE 15%

00:13:21,601 --> 00:13:23,102
WITH NO CONTINGENCIES,

00:13:23,102 --> 00:13:26,539
SO THE RISK OF ME PRODUCING IT
ON TV's ON MY SIDE.

00:13:26,539 --> 00:13:30,843
DON'T YOU THINK I'M GONNA BE
MOTIVATED TO MAKE THIS HAPPEN?

00:13:30,843 --> 00:13:33,513
I'VE MADE AN OFFER, REBECCA.

00:13:33,513 --> 00:13:38,251
YOU HAVE TO MAKE A DECISION
RIGHT NOW.

00:13:38,251 --> 00:13:41,854
20%, $100,000.
YES.

00:13:41,854 --> 00:13:43,456
OKAY.
CRAP!

00:13:43,456 --> 00:13:46,426
(Daymond) AAH! (laughs)
(Robert) YEAH! VERY GOOD!

00:13:46,426 --> 00:13:48,795
OKAY. ALL RIGHT. THANK YOU.

00:13:48,795 --> 00:13:50,563
KEVIN. WHOO!

00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:53,099
ONE FOR THE BOYS.
ONE FOR THE BOYS.

00:13:53,099 --> 00:13:56,536
YEAH!
(O'Leary) REBECCA, WHAT HAPPENED
TO ALL THE LOVE?

00:13:56,536 --> 00:13:59,539
I <i>DO</i> LOVE YOU, BARBARA!
BYE. AAH!

00:14:01,341 --> 00:14:04,677
KEVIN, YOU'RE A DIRTY DOG.
(Robert)
DO YOU REALLY HAVE A CAT?

00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:07,280
I LOVE CATS. I DON'T HAVE ONE.
I LOVE THEM, THOUGH. (laughs)

00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:09,849
THEY MAKE MONEY, OKAY?
(Robert laughs)

00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:11,851
WITHOUT "SHARK TANK,"
I CAN'T EVEN IMAGINE.

00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:13,853
I'D BE SELLING THEM
ONE AT A TIME, YOU KNOW,

00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:16,856
ACROSS THE INTERNET. AND THIS IS
GONNA MAKE THE PRODUCT HUGE.

00:14:16,856 --> 00:14:19,859
I FEEL IT IN MY BONES,
I FEEL IT IN MY SOUL

00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:22,362
THAT THIS IS THE NEXT STEP
FOR THIS COMPANY.

00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:26,733
♪♪♪

00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:30,603
<i>LAST SEASON, WE SAW JEFF COHEN</i>
<i>AND HIS SON JOSH</i>

00:14:30,603 --> 00:14:32,872
<i>PASS ON $1 MILLION OFFER</i>
<i>FROM THE SHARKS</i>

00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,874
<i>FOR THEIR VOYAGE‐AIR GUITAR.</i>

00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:37,744
I DON'T ACCEPT THE DEALS
ON THE TABLE.

00:14:37,744 --> 00:14:41,581
I'M STUNNED OF YOUR GREED.

00:14:41,581 --> 00:14:44,650
<i>LET'S SEE</i>
<i>WHAT THEY'RE UP TO NOW.</i>

00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:47,720
♪♪♪

00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:50,990
WHEN WE LEFT "SHARK TANK,"
PEOPLE THOUGHT WE WERE CRAZY

00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:53,059
FOR TURNING DOWN $1 MILLION.

00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:57,063
VOYAGE‐AIR GUITAR IS THE WORLD'S
FIRST FOLDABLE GUITAR.

00:14:57,063 --> 00:15:00,500
EVEN THOUGH WE DIDN'T GET A DEAL
WITH THE SHARKS,

00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,602
GOING ON "SHARK TANK" WAS
ONE OF THE BEST THINGS

00:15:02,602 --> 00:15:04,637
THAT WE COULD'VE DONE
FOR THIS COMPANY.

00:15:04,637 --> 00:15:06,139
IT VALIDATED THE PRODUCT,

00:15:06,139 --> 00:15:08,207
GAVE US A TREMENDOUS AMOUNT
OF EXPOSURE.

00:15:08,207 --> 00:15:10,376
I PASSED ON THE DEAL
WITH THE SHARKS

00:15:10,376 --> 00:15:12,678
BECAUSE THEY WANTED TO LICENSE
THE PATENTED HINGE

00:15:12,678 --> 00:15:15,481
TO OTHER GUITAR MANUFACTURERS
AND SIT BACK

00:15:15,481 --> 00:15:17,650
AND COLLECT ROYALTIES. QUITE
FRANKLY, I WASN'T CONVINCED

00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:21,020
THAT LICENSING IS THE RIGHT WAY
TO START THE COMPANY.

00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:23,089
THE GUITARS ARE SELLING
INCREDIBLY WELL.

00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:25,858
OUR SALES HAVE EXCEEDED
ONE AND A HALF MILLION DOLLARS,

00:15:25,858 --> 00:15:28,261
AND WE'RE GOING TO MOST LIKELY
DOUBLE THAT IN REVENUE

00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:31,731
DURING 2011.
WE ALSO JUST CAME OUT
WITH ELECTRIC VOYAGE‐AIR,

00:15:31,731 --> 00:15:34,667
WHICH IS SO POPULAR. IN FACT,
IT JUST BECAME SOLD OUT.

00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:38,070
LOTS OF BIG CELEBRITIES USE
OUR VOYAGE‐AIR GUITAR.

00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:42,575
BIG ARTISTS LIKE JOHN OATES
OF HALL &amp; OATES, BRAD PAISLEY,

00:15:42,575 --> 00:15:45,111
WILLIE NELSON, AND MANY OTHER
WELL‐KNOWN ARTISTS.

00:15:45,111 --> 00:15:46,979
VOYAGE‐AIR GUITAR

00:15:46,979 --> 00:15:49,882
WOULD NOT BE NEARLY
AS SUCCESSFUL AS IT IS TODAY

00:15:49,882 --> 00:15:51,984
WITHOUT THE EXPOSURE
FROM "SHARK TANK."

00:15:51,984 --> 00:15:54,754
♪♪♪

00:16:00,193 --> 00:16:02,195
♪♪♪

00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:05,698
<i>NEXT UP IS KIM PREIS,</i>

00:16:05,698 --> 00:16:07,300
<i>WITH A T‐SHIRT COMPANY</i>

00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,869
<i>ESPECIALLY DESIGNED</i>
<i>FOR EXPECTING MOMS.</i>

00:16:23,149 --> 00:16:24,851
MY NAME IS KIM PREIS,

00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:26,953
MY COMPANY IS SAMSON MARTIN,

00:16:26,953 --> 00:16:29,522
AND I AM SEEKING $50,000

00:16:29,522 --> 00:16:32,992
IN EXCHANGE FOR 15% EQUITY
IN MY BUSINESS.

00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:36,262
A FEW YEARS AGO,
I CAME UP WITH THE IDEA

00:16:36,262 --> 00:16:39,632
BECAUSE ALL OF MY GIRLFRIENDS
WERE PREGNANT AT THE TIME,

00:16:39,632 --> 00:16:42,101
AND THE OBVIOUS QUESTION
THAT THEY'RE ASKED IS

00:16:42,101 --> 00:16:44,203
WHEN ARE YOU DUE?

00:16:44,203 --> 00:16:47,173
SO I THOUGHT, HOW LOGICAL IT
WOULD BE TO PUT IT ON A T‐SHIRT?

00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:50,209
WE HAD LAUNCHED
WITH THE "DUE IN" TEE,

00:16:50,209 --> 00:16:52,478
AND EXPANDED THE COLLECTION

00:16:52,478 --> 00:16:55,381
TO VARIOUS OTHER EXECUTIONS.

00:16:55,381 --> 00:17:00,152
I ORIGINALLY POSITIONED THE LINE
IN UPSCALE BOUTIQUES.

00:17:00,152 --> 00:17:03,990
MY GOAL WAS REALLY TO ALIGN IT
WITH HIGHER‐END BRANDS,

00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:06,459
BUT DUE TO THE RECESSION,
THE BOUTIQUE BUSINESS

00:17:06,459 --> 00:17:08,661
HAS BEEN HIT TREMENDOUSLY HARD.

00:17:08,661 --> 00:17:12,465
I NEED TO REPOSITION THE BRAND
AND REALLY COME UP WITH A WAY

00:17:12,465 --> 00:17:16,402
TO PRODUCE
A MORE ECONOMICAL COLLECTION

00:17:16,402 --> 00:17:19,038
AND TAKE IT TO MASS RETAILERS.

00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,340
THIS IS A PROVEN WINNER.

00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:24,710
I'VE DONE TREMENDOUS SALES.
I HAVE GOTTEN TREMENDOUS PRESS.

00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:28,147
I JUST NEED THE CONTACTS,
THE DOORS TO BE OPEN,

00:17:28,147 --> 00:17:30,049
THE PROPER FINANCIAL INJECTION

00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:33,953
TO REPOSITION THE BRAND
AND GROW IT FURTHER.

00:17:33,953 --> 00:17:36,822
LET'S START
WITH THE SALES NUMBERS.
(Robert) YEAH.

00:17:36,822 --> 00:17:39,792
LAST YEAR I DID $90,000
IN SALES. I'VE BEEN IN BUSINESS

00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:42,295
FOR 6 YEARS. I'VE DONE
A TOTAL OF $1.4 MILLION

00:17:42,295 --> 00:17:44,096
OUT OF MY BASEMENT.

00:17:44,096 --> 00:17:47,466
SO HAVE YOUR SALES GONE UP
AND THEN STARTED DROPPING?

00:17:47,466 --> 00:17:50,269
YES.
SO WHAT WERE THE SALES
AT THEIR PEAK?

00:17:50,269 --> 00:17:53,172
$400,000.
AND THEY DROPPED TO $90,000?

00:17:53,172 --> 00:17:55,875
MM‐HMM.
HOW MUCH DO YOU SELL THESE FOR?

00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:57,877
UH, THEY RANGE.
THE TANK TOPS ARE

00:17:57,877 --> 00:17:59,745
ANYWHERE BETWEEN $38 AND $42.

00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:04,283
THE LONG SLEEVES ARE
ANYWHERE BETWEEN $55 AND $60.

00:18:04,283 --> 00:18:07,353
CAN YOU STOP ANYBODY ELSE
FROM PUTTING THIS ON A T‐SHIRT?

00:18:07,353 --> 00:18:09,989
I HAVE A TRADEMARK ON "DUE IN."

00:18:09,989 --> 00:18:12,391
THE WORDS "DUE IN"‐‐
NO ONE ELSE COULD USE?

00:18:12,391 --> 00:18:15,328
"DUE"‐‐WHEN I LAUNCHED
THE LINE BACK IN '04,

00:18:15,328 --> 00:18:18,097
I GOT TREMENDOUS AMOUNT OF
PRESS, CELEBRITY RECOGNITION.

00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:21,601
JENNIFER GARNER, ANGELINA JOLIE,
BRITNEY SPEARS.

00:18:21,601 --> 00:18:24,303
KIM, YOU'RE A T‐SHIRT COMPANY.
THE OBJECTIVE IS

00:18:24,303 --> 00:18:27,306
TO SELL MORE T‐SHIRTS, MAKE MORE
MONEY. WE ALL AGREE ON THAT.

00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:30,743
YEAH. RIGHT.
YOU HAVE PICKED A SUBSEGMENT
OF A SUBSEGMENT.

00:18:30,743 --> 00:18:33,045
IN OTHER WORDS,
I CAN'T SELL TO MEN.

00:18:33,045 --> 00:18:35,147
THAT'S 50% OF THE MARKET GONE...
SURE.

00:18:35,147 --> 00:18:37,550
BUT I CAN'T SELL
TO ALL WOMEN EITHER.

00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:40,553
I CAN ONLY SELL
TO THE PREGNANT ONES. THAT'S IT.
6 MILLION.

00:18:40,553 --> 00:18:43,022
OKAY, BUT I'M SAYING
IT'S VERY HARD

00:18:43,022 --> 00:18:46,058
TO GET TO MY TARGET MARKET
BECAUSE THEY TEND TO BE PREGNANT

00:18:46,058 --> 00:18:49,895
FOR ONLY NINE MONTHS.
(Robert) I LIKE THAT APPROACH.
I LIKE THE FACT

00:18:49,895 --> 00:18:53,833
THAT YOU FOUND
A VERY NICHE MARKET.
THE BEAUTY
OF THE MATERNITY MARKET IS

00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:56,469
YOU HAVE A NEW CUSTOMER
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

00:18:56,469 --> 00:18:59,205
WHOLEHEARTEDLY AGREE.
WHEN YOU'RE PREGNANT,

00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:02,708
YOUR OLD CLOTHES DON'T FIT.
YOU'RE A FORCED CUSTOMER.
YES.

00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:05,578
MY ISSUE IS NOT THE MARKET.

00:19:05,578 --> 00:19:08,381
MY ISSUE IS YOU WERE HOT
A FEW YEARS AGO.

00:19:08,381 --> 00:19:13,252
YOU'RE SAYING
SHE'S NOT HOT NOW?
KEVIN, MY MIND IS NOT
IN THE GUTTER LIKE YOURS.

00:19:13,252 --> 00:19:15,454
OH.
I'M SIMPLY TALKING ABOUT
HER BUSINESS.

00:19:15,454 --> 00:19:17,323
SHE IS A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN,

00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:19,392
OF COURSE,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE IMPLYING.

00:19:19,392 --> 00:19:21,927
BUT YOU HIT SALES OF $400,000,
RECESSION HIT,

00:19:21,927 --> 00:19:25,398
AND THEN YOU KIND OF HIT BOTTOM.
CAN YOU BE HOT TWICE?

00:19:25,398 --> 00:19:27,867
CAN THAT BABY BE BORN AGAIN?

00:19:27,867 --> 00:19:29,268
ABSOLUTELY.

00:19:29,268 --> 00:19:31,871
I KNOW I CAN DO IT AGAIN
BECAUSE, I MEAN,

00:19:31,871 --> 00:19:36,275
THIS IS‐‐THIS TOOK A GREAT DEAL
OF THOUGHT IN DEVELOPING.

00:19:36,275 --> 00:19:38,344
A LOT OF THE MATERNITY T‐SHIRTS
OUT THERE‐‐

00:19:38,344 --> 00:19:41,180
THEY'RE NOT FLATTERING
TO WOMEN.

00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:44,684
THEY'RE NOT MAKING THEM
LOOK BEAUTIFUL AND SEXY.

00:19:44,684 --> 00:19:48,521
WHEN I LAUNCHED THE LINE, IT WAS
ABOUT ESTABLISHING A BRAND AND‐‐
WELL, HOW DO YOU THINK
YOU'VE DONE THERE?

00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:51,357
I'VE NEVER HEARD
OF SAMSON MARTIN.
WELL, YOU'RE NOT PREGNANT.

00:19:51,357 --> 00:19:54,827
I KNOW, BUT THAT'S MY PROBLEM‐‐
I CAN ONLY SELL IT

00:19:54,827 --> 00:19:57,830
TO PEOPLE THAT ARE PREGNANT.
(Barbara) YOU SAID
YOU WANTED REPOSITIONING.

00:19:57,830 --> 00:20:00,399
THAT MEANS YOU WANT TO MAKE
A CHEAPER‐PRICED BRAND?

00:20:00,399 --> 00:20:03,436
YES.
THEN LET'S SAY YOU DO.
THEN WHAT DO YOU DO WITH

00:20:03,436 --> 00:20:05,104
THAT CHEAPER T‐SHIRT?

00:20:05,104 --> 00:20:07,406
I TAKE IT
TO A LARGER RETAILER.

00:20:07,406 --> 00:20:11,477
I CAN'T RELY ON
THESE SMALLER BOUTIQUES TO‐‐

00:20:11,477 --> 00:20:13,779
FOR ECONOMIC GROWTH,
I CAN'T DO IT.

00:20:13,779 --> 00:20:15,948
I'M THINKING TARGET.
I'M THINKING JCPenney,

00:20:15,948 --> 00:20:19,752
I'M THINKING KOHL'S.
I'M THINKING buybuy BABY.
(Daymond) HAVE YOU TALKED
TO THEM?

00:20:19,752 --> 00:20:22,054
I HAVE NOT.
(Robert) WHY?

00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:25,124
I DON'T HAVE
THE PROPER CONTACTS.
YOU BUILT A BUSINESS.
YOU'VE BEEN IN BUSINESS

00:20:25,124 --> 00:20:28,127
FOR ALL THIS TIME.
YOU DON'T HAVE THE PROPER...
YEAH.

00:20:28,127 --> 00:20:30,896
YOU CAN'T PICK UP A PHONE
AND MAKE A CALL?

00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:34,633
I HAVE MADE PHONE CALLS.
I HAVE NOT...
(Barbara) CONNECTED.

00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:36,368
YOU WANT $50,000.
YES.

00:20:36,368 --> 00:20:39,238
WHAT‐‐WHERE YOU GONNA GO
WITH THAT?

00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:41,240
THE MONEY WOULD BE
FOR MARKETING, PRODUCTION,

00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:44,877
MANUFACTURING, AND TO
ESSENTIALLY FILL THE ORDERS.

00:20:44,877 --> 00:20:47,546
