WHAT HAVE YOU DONE
FOR ME LATELY?

00:22:51,670 --> 00:22:54,740
WHO CARES ABOUT THE PAST?
WHAT ABOUT RIGHT NOW? IT‐‐

00:22:54,740 --> 00:22:57,109
UH, I‐I BELIEVE
THAT THIS BRAND

00:22:57,109 --> 00:22:59,511
AND THE ACTUAL PRODUCT IS
A WINNER.

00:22:59,511 --> 00:23:01,647
I'M STUCK
ON THIS SUBSEGMENT PROBLEM

00:23:01,647 --> 00:23:04,183
BECAUSE I CAN SELL T‐SHIRTS
TO 250 MILLION PEOPLE

00:23:04,183 --> 00:23:07,186
OR 6 MILLION PEOPLE.
LET ME THINK ABOUT THAT.
RIGHT.

00:23:07,186 --> 00:23:09,221
HMM. 250,000,000.
BUT‐‐

00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:12,424
KIM, I GOTTA TELL YOU, THIS IS
THE T‐SHIRT DEAL FROM HELL.

00:23:12,424 --> 00:23:15,194
YOU CAN'T SELL IT TO ANYBODY
EXCEPT PREGNANT WOMEN,

00:23:15,194 --> 00:23:17,696
SALES ARE GOING DOWN,
THE MARKET'S GETTING SOFT,

00:23:17,696 --> 00:23:20,366
PRICE POINTS ARE COMING DOWN.

00:23:20,366 --> 00:23:23,535
I MEAN, I'M TRYING TO FIND
SOMETHING, <i>ANYTHING.</i>

00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:26,538
BUT NO, IT'S ALL DEATH
AND DESTRUCTION IN YOUR STORY.

00:23:26,538 --> 00:23:28,274
IT'S HORRIBLE. I'M OUT.

00:23:29,875 --> 00:23:31,510
(Robert) WOW. THAT WAS...

00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:33,879
WOW.
WOW.

00:23:33,879 --> 00:23:35,414
WOW.
WOW. THAT'S HARSH.

00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:37,049
WELL, AM I WRONG?

00:23:37,049 --> 00:23:41,120
TALK ABOUT THROWING THE, UH,
BABY WITH THE BATHWATER.

00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:44,189
HE'S NEGATIVE.
DO YOU HAVE ANY DOUBT
I'M TELLING THE TRUTH?

00:23:44,189 --> 00:23:47,393
I DON'T THINK I'M A, YOU KNOW,
A DEATH INVESTMENT.

00:23:47,393 --> 00:23:50,229
BUT I‐I WOULD BE KILLING MONEY
IF I GAVE IT TO YOU.

00:23:50,229 --> 00:23:53,399
I ONLY WORRY ABOUT THE DEATH
OF THE MONEY. THAT'S IT.

00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,037
OKAY. THANK YOU SO MUCH.

00:23:58,037 --> 00:24:01,840
WHAT ARE YOU THANKING US FOR?
BECAUSE SHE'S POLITE.
THAT'S WHY.

00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:04,643
BECAUSE I'M A LADY.
(Robert) THAT'S RIGHT.

00:24:04,643 --> 00:24:07,813
YOU DON'T REALLY WANT TO THANK
ME FOR THAT INFORMATION, DO YOU?

00:24:07,813 --> 00:24:11,150
NO, BUT WHAT‐‐
W‐WHY ARE YOU, UH...
I'M JUST TRYING TO BE HONEST.
THAT'S IT.

00:24:11,150 --> 00:24:15,054
(Barbara) BUT SHE'S NOT ARGUING.
LEAVE HER ALONE.
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES THE TRUTH IS
THE BEST MEDICINE.

00:24:15,054 --> 00:24:18,724
FINE, KEVIN. ENOUGH.
LET'S GO.
(Robert) SHE'S JUST BEING NICE.

00:24:18,724 --> 00:24:22,227
SHE THANKED YOU
FOR LISTENING TO HER.
SHE WAS‐‐YOU DON'T WANT
TO HEAR THIS.

00:24:22,227 --> 00:24:25,297
(Robert) I THINK IT'S VERY
PROFESSIONAL TO THANK SOMEBODY.
THANK YOU.

00:24:26,932 --> 00:24:28,701
I HATE THE FACT

00:24:28,701 --> 00:24:32,538
WE MAKE PEOPLE FEEL SO BAD.
(O'Leary) YOU KNOW, ROBERT,

00:24:32,538 --> 00:24:35,708
WHAT'S DEPRESSING ABOUT YOU IS
YOU CAN'T DEAL WITH THE TRUTH,

00:24:35,708 --> 00:24:38,110
BECAUSE THE MONEY
WILL NEVER LIE.
KEVIN‐‐

00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:42,014
THAT MONEY IS TELLING ME
THAT THIS IS A LOSER.
KEVIN, YOU'RE NOT
GONNA BELIEVE THIS,

00:24:42,014 --> 00:24:44,950
BUT THERE ARE OTHER PEOPLE'S
TRUTHS THAN YOURS IN THE WORLD.

00:24:44,950 --> 00:24:48,087
IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE.
THERE'S ONLY ONE TRUTH IN MAKING
MONEY‐‐YOU EITHER MAKE IT

00:24:48,087 --> 00:24:51,256
OR YOU LOSE IT. THAT'S IT.
SHE'S LOSING IT.
(Barbara) OKAY, WE'RE DONE.

00:24:51,256 --> 00:24:54,093
OKAY, TIME OUT, GUYS.
WE'VE BEEN HERE.
SHE MAY RECOVER.

00:24:54,093 --> 00:24:56,161
LET'S GO. TIME OUT.

00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:59,732
(sighs) I DEFINITELY BELIEVE
THAT...

00:24:59,732 --> 00:25:02,701
COMING AT ME, TELLING ME
THAT MY BUSINESS IS DEAD

00:25:02,701 --> 00:25:05,037
AND THAT THIS IS
INVESTMENT SUICIDE

00:25:05,037 --> 00:25:07,906
WAS A LITTLE, UH...

00:25:07,906 --> 00:25:09,908
IT WAS A LITTLE DISRESPECTFUL

00:25:09,908 --> 00:25:12,778
AND A LITTLE UNNECESSARY.

